        "hero_headline": "Coastline vs AG1: Which Longevity Supplement Is Actually Worth It?",
        "hero_subheadline": "Both brands promise better health. But which one actually delivers? We compared ingredients, clinical evidence, pricing, and real user feedback.",
        "hero_author": "By Dr. James Chen",
        "hero_author_title": "Clinical Nutrition Researcher",
        "hero_cta_text": "See the Full Comparison",
        "intro_body_1": "The supplement market has exploded. AG1 has dominated with aggressive marketing and influencer partnerships. But several science-first alternatives have emerged. Coastline is one of them.",
        "bridge_1_headline": "The study AG1 probably wishes you had not seen",
        "bridge_1_p1": "For years, AG1 has been the default recommendation. You have seen it everywhere -- podcast ads, YouTube sponsorships, Instagram stories. It became the supplement that people bought because everyone else seemed to be buying it.",
        "bridge_1_p2": "Then AG1 published its own clinical trial. The results were supposed to validate what millions of subscribers already believed. Instead, the data told a very different story.",
        "bridge_1_p3": "Here is what the study actually found -- and why it matters for anyone paying $79 a month.",
