        "pixie_dust_headline": "The pixie dusting problem",
        "pixie_dust_body": "AG1 contains 75 ingredients in a single scoop. That sounds impressive until you do the math. Imagine splitting a single glass of water among 75 people. Each person gets a few drops. That is what happens when you cram 75 ingredients into one serving -- most are present in trace amounts far below what clinical trials use.",
        "bridge_2_headline": "So we pulled the data",
        "bridge_2_p1": "That is a lot to take in. A product used by millions, backed by some of the biggest names on the internet, and its own clinical trial could not demonstrate significant benefits over a placebo.",
        "bridge_2_p2": "So we did what any rational person would do. We pulled the publicly available data on both AG1 and Coastline and laid them side by side. Not marketing claims. Just the ingredients, the doses, the clinical evidence, and the price.",
        "bridge_2_p3": "Here is exactly what we found when we compared them head to head.",
        "price_headline": "What you're actually paying for",
        "price_framing": "$0.67/day more for ingredients proven to work at doses proven to matter. You are not paying for ingredient count. You are paying for ingredient doses that actually work.",
